$neighborhoods = @(
  @{ slug="graydon-hill"; display="Graydon Hill"; era="2015+"; transit="approximately 18-22 minutes from our Edmonton hub via 170 Street SW and Ellerslie Road"; streets="Graydon Hill Boulevard, Graydon Hill Common, and Graydon Hill Way"; dw_brands="Samsung, Bosch, LG, Frigidaire"; w_brands="Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Maytag"; f_brands="Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Frigidaire"
    dw_body="Graydon Hill is a 2015+ new-build family neighbourhood in southwest Edmonton, part of the Heritage Valley development area adjacent to Windermere. Kitchens arrive fully outfitted with stainless Frigidaire, Samsung, and Whirlpool appliances. Bosch and LG dishwashers are popular upgrades that homeowners install after possession. Edmonton EPCOR water hardness of 170-200 mg/L accelerates mineral scale in spray arms and inlet screens, causing wash quality failures at 4-7 years. Control board faults and drain pump issues are the leading calls from this neighbourhood. We stock Samsung and Bosch parts for Graydon Hill dispatches as a matter of routine."
    w_body="Graydon Hill is a 2015+ new-build family neighbourhood in southwest Edmonton, part of the Heritage Valley development area adjacent to Windermere. Streets like Graydon Hill Boulevard wind through this master-planned community of two-storey single-family homes and townhouses. Samsung, LG, and Whirlpool front-load washers are the dominant brands. Appliances installed at possession are now 5-10 years into service, with drain pump failures, bearing noise, and inlet valve scale from Edmonton EPCOR hard water among the most common repair calls."
    f_body="Graydon Hill is a 2015+ new-build family neighbourhood in southwest Edmonton, part of the Heritage Valley development area adjacent to Windermere. Samsung French-door refrigerators and LG counter-depth fridges are the most common fridge brands in this newer community. At 5-10 years of age, these units are generating their first ice maker module failures, inlet valve scale issues from Edmonton EPCOR 170-200 mg/L hard water, and evaporator fan faults. We carry OEM Samsung and LG fridge parts for Graydon Hill dispatches." }

  @{ slug="maple"; display="Maple"; era="2010s"; transit="approximately 20-25 minutes from our Edmonton hub via Anthony Henday Drive and 17 Street SE"; streets="Maple Road SE, Maple Crest Boulevard, and Maple Square"; dw_brands="Whirlpool, Samsung, LG, Bosch"; w_brands="Whirlpool, Samsung, LG, Maytag"; f_brands="Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Frigidaire"
    dw_body="Maple is a 2010s family neighbourhood in southeast Edmonton, part of The Meadows master-planned area east of 17 Street SE. Builder dishwashers are 10-14 years old and in peak repair demand. Edmonton EPCOR water hardness of 170-200 mg/L accelerates mineral scale in spray nozzles and inlet valves. Drain pump failure and control board faults are the most common calls we receive from Maple homeowners. Bosch and KitchenAid dishwashers are common upgrades in Maple's renovated kitchens and carry their own service profile."
    w_body="Maple is a 2010s family neighbourhood in southeast Edmonton, part of The Meadows master-planned area east of 17 Street SE. The community features single-family homes and semi-detached properties along Maple Road SE and Maple Crest Boulevard. Whirlpool, Maytag, Samsung, and LG washers are the dominant brands across this era. These units are now 10-14 years old, entering peak repair demand. Drum bearing noise, drain pump failure, and lid switch faults are the most common washer calls from Maple."
    f_body="Maple is a 2010s family neighbourhood in southeast Edmonton, part of The Meadows master-planned area east of 17 Street SE. Samsung and LG French-door refrigerators are the most common fridge brands. At 10-14 years of age, these units are generating ice maker module failures, water inlet valve scale from EPCOR 170-200 mg/L hard water, defrost heater burnouts, and evaporator fan faults. Builder-grade Whirlpool and Frigidaire fridges are also common and showing compressor wear at this service age." }

  @{ slug="potter-greens"; display="Potter Greens"; era="1990s-2000s"; transit="approximately 22-28 minutes from our Edmonton hub via Anthony Henday Drive and 87 Avenue"; streets="Potter Greens Drive, Potter Greens Boulevard, and Riverside Drive"; dw_brands="Maytag, Whirlpool, Frigidaire, KitchenAid"; w_brands="Maytag, Whirlpool, Kenmore, Amana"; f_brands="Maytag, Whirlpool, Frigidaire, Kenmore"
    dw_body="Potter Greens is a 1990s-2000s family neighbourhood in west Edmonton, part of the Lewis Farms area set alongside the Riverside Golf Course. Dishwashers installed at possession are now 20-25 years old. Maytag, Whirlpool, and Frigidaire are the most common brands. Control board replacement, drain pump failure, and door gasket degradation are the dominant repair categories. Edmonton hard water compounds scale damage over decades of service. Many Potter Greens homeowners have also upgraded to Bosch or KitchenAid dishwashers in the past 5-10 years, adding a newer service profile to our call sheet."
    w_body="Potter Greens is a 1990s-2000s family neighbourhood in west Edmonton, part of the Lewis Farms area set alongside the Riverside Golf Course on the north Saskatchewan River escarpment. Homes along Potter Greens Drive and Potter Greens Boulevard were built in the late 1990s through mid-2000s. Maytag, Whirlpool, and Kenmore washers are the dominant brands, now 20-25 years old. Drum bearing failure, pump motor burnout, and transmission wear are common at this age. We carry OEM drum bearings and pump motors for this appliance generation."
    f_body="Potter Greens is a 1990s-2000s family neighbourhood in west Edmonton, part of the Lewis Farms area set alongside the Riverside Golf Course. Fridges installed at possession are Maytag, Whirlpool, Frigidaire, and Kenmore  -  now 20-30 years old. Compressor failure, evaporator fan burnout, and defrost heater failure are common at this service age. Many homeowners have also upgraded to Samsung or LG French-door fridges in the past decade, adding a newer service profile. We carry OEM parts for both generations." }

  @{ slug="stewart-greens"; display="Stewart Greens"; era="2010s"; transit="approximately 22-26 minutes from our Edmonton hub via Anthony Henday Drive and 87 Avenue"; streets="Stewart Greens Boulevard, Stewart Drive, and Riverside Drive West"; dw_brands="Samsung, Bosch, LG, Whirlpool"; w_brands="LG, Samsung, Whirlpool, Maytag"; f_brands="Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Frigidaire"
    dw_body="Stewart Greens is a 2010s Lewis Farms neighbourhood in west Edmonton where appliances installed at build are now 10-15 years old. EPCOR hard water at 170-200 mg/L accelerates spray arm mineral scale and inlet valve failure in dishwashers throughout Stewart Greens. Samsung, Bosch, and LG dishwashers are the most common brands on our call sheet. Wash quality issues from scale buildup, E-code faults on Bosch units, and drain pump failures are the top repair categories. We carry OEM parts for Samsung, Bosch, and LG dishwasher platforms for Stewart Greens dispatches."
    w_body="Stewart Greens is a 2010s family neighbourhood in west Edmonton, part of the Lewis Farms area adjacent to Potter Greens. Developed between 2008 and 2016, homes along Stewart Greens Boulevard feature mid-range to premium appliance packages. LG and Samsung front-load washers were popular choices during this build window. These appliances are now 10-15 years old, generating drain pump failures, drum bearing noise, door boot seal leaks, and error code faults. We carry OEM bearings and pump assemblies for LG and Samsung washer platforms."
    f_body="Stewart Greens is a 2010s family neighbourhood in west Edmonton, part of the Lewis Farms area. Samsung French-door refrigerators and LG side-by-side units are the most common fridge brands in Stewart Greens. At 10-15 years of age, these units are generating ice maker module failures, inlet valve scale from EPCOR 170-200 mg/L hard water, defrost heater burnouts, and control board faults. We carry OEM Samsung and LG fridge parts for Stewart Greens dispatches." }

  @{ slug="york"; display="York"; era="2000s"; transit="approximately 20-25 minutes from our Edmonton hub via 97 Street NW and Castledowns Road"; streets="York Drive, York Close, and Castledowns Road"; dw_brands="Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Frigidaire"; w_brands="LG, Samsung, Whirlpool, Kenmore"; f_brands="Samsung, LG, Frigidaire, Whirlpool"
    dw_body="York is a 2000s northeast Edmonton neighbourhood where dishwashers installed at possession are now 15-20 years old. Samsung, LG, and Whirlpool are the dominant brands. Drain pump failure, control board faults, and inlet valve degradation are the most frequent calls. Edmonton EPCOR hard water at 170-200 mg/L compounds long-term spray arm scale buildup, causing wash quality failures that many York homeowners initially attribute to detergent issues. Many York residents have also upgraded to Bosch dishwashers over the past decade, adding a newer service profile."
    w_body="York is a 2000s family neighbourhood in northeast Edmonton, located in the Casselman-Steele Heights planning area near the Castledowns Road and 137 Avenue corridor. Built predominantly between 2000 and 2010, York features a mix of single-family homes and townhouses. LG, Samsung, and Whirlpool washers are the dominant brands. These appliances are now 15-25 years into service. Drum bearing failures, drive belt breakage, and pump motor burnout are common at this age. We carry OEM bearings for LG and Samsung front-loaders as standard truck stock for northeast Edmonton dispatches."
    f_body="York is a 2000s family neighbourhood in northeast Edmonton located in the Casselman-Steele Heights planning area. Samsung and LG French-door refrigerators are the most common upgraded brands, while builder-grade Whirlpool and Frigidaire fridges from the original build window are now 15-25 years old. Compressor failures, defrost heater burnouts, evaporator fan faults, and ice maker module failures are the most common repair categories from York. We carry OEM parts for both generations of fridges common in York." }

  @{ slug="highlands"; display="Highlands"; era="1910s-1930s"; transit="approximately 10-15 minutes from our Edmonton hub via 82 Street and 112 Avenue"; streets="Ada Boulevard, 112 Avenue, and the Highlands Golf Course corridor"; dw_brands="Miele, Bosch, Fisher and Paykel, KitchenAid"; w_brands="Miele, Bosch, LG, Samsung"; f_brands="Sub-Zero, Miele, Bosch, KitchenAid"
    dw_body="Highlands is a 1910s-1930s heritage neighbourhood in northeast Edmonton where fully renovated kitchens feature Miele, Bosch, and Sub-Zero appliances. Edmonton EPCOR hard water at 170-200 mg/L causes mineral scale in spray arms and inlet valves of even premium dishwashers. Miele E-code faults and Bosch E15/E22 errors are the most common calls from Highlands homes. The heritage utility room configurations in Highlands properties can present access challenges  -  our technicians carry slim-profile diagnostic tools and are experienced with non-standard installation depths common in these character kitchens."
    w_body="Highlands is one of Edmonton's most historically significant neighbourhoods, developed between the 1910s and 1930s on the north bank of the North Saskatchewan River valley in northeast Edmonton. Streets like Ada Boulevard and 112 Avenue are lined with heritage Craftsman, Georgian, and Colonial Revival homes with substantially renovated kitchens. Miele and Bosch front-load washers are common in these high-end renovations. LG and Samsung washers appear in secondary bathrooms and basement laundry rooms. We carry OEM parts for Miele and Bosch washer platforms as standard truck stock for Highlands dispatches."
    f_body="Highlands is a 1910s-1930s heritage neighbourhood in northeast Edmonton where renovated kitchens feature Sub-Zero built-in refrigerators, Miele integrated fridges, and Bosch French-door units. These are among the highest-value appliances we service in Edmonton. Heritage utility room access configurations can complicate fridge removal for repair. Sub-Zero compressor issues and Miele refrigerant system faults are the most common premium repair calls. We carry OEM Sub-Zero and Miele fridge parts as standard truck stock for Highlands dispatches." }

  @{ slug="bannerman"; display="Bannerman"; era="1980s"; transit="approximately 18-22 minutes from our Edmonton hub via 97 Street and 167 Avenue"; streets="167 Avenue NW, 50 Street NW, and Bannerman Road"; dw_brands="Frigidaire, Maytag, Whirlpool, Kenmore"; w_brands="Maytag, Whirlpool, Kenmore, Frigidaire"; f_brands="Frigidaire, Kenmore, Whirlpool, Maytag"
    dw_body="Bannerman is a 1980s Clareview neighbourhood in northeast Edmonton where many dishwashers are 20-35 years old. Frigidaire, Maytag, and Whirlpool are the dominant brands across two appliance generations. Drain pump failures, door gasket leaks, and control board failures are the most common repair categories. Hard water scale from Edmonton's EPCOR supply at 170-200 mg/L compounds long-term wear in dishwashers that have not been maintained with regular descale cycles. A growing number of Bannerman homeowners have upgraded to Samsung or LG dishwashers in recent years, adding a newer service profile to our call sheet."
    w_body="Bannerman is a 1980s family neighbourhood in northeast Edmonton, one of the Clareview area sub-communities situated along 167 Avenue NW and the 50 Street NW corridor. Developed primarily between 1980 and 1990, Bannerman features two-storey and bi-level single-family homes. A significant proportion of Bannerman homes operate second-generation appliances from the early 2000s  -  Maytag, Whirlpool, and Kenmore washers now 20-25 years old. Drum transmission failure, pump motor burnout, and agitator coupler wear are common at this age. We carry OEM transmission parts for older Whirlpool and Maytag platforms."
    f_body="Bannerman is a 1980s family neighbourhood in northeast Edmonton, part of the Clareview area. Fridges installed at possession are Frigidaire, Kenmore, Whirlpool, and Maytag  -  now 20-40 years old. Many have been replaced, but second-generation fridges from the early 2000s are now mid-life at 20-25 years. Compressor failure, evaporator fan burnout, defrost heater failure, and refrigerant leaks are common at this service age. We handle both the older original units and newer Samsung or LG French-door upgrades that Bannerman homeowners have installed." }

  @{ slug="larkspur"; display="Larkspur"; era="2000s"; transit="approximately 20-25 minutes from our Edmonton hub via Anthony Henday Drive and 17 Street SE"; streets="Larkspur Road SE, Larkspur Boulevard SE, and Larkspur Gate"; dw_brands="Whirlpool, Samsung, LG, Bosch"; w_brands="Whirlpool, Samsung, LG, Maytag"; f_brands="Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Frigidaire"
    dw_body="Larkspur is a 2000s Meadows neighbourhood in southeast Edmonton where dishwashers are 12-22 years old. Whirlpool, Samsung, LG, and Bosch are the dominant brands. Spray arm mineral scale from EPCOR 170-200 mg/L hard water is a leading cause of wash quality failures. Drain pump and control board faults are the top repair categories. Bosch and KitchenAid dishwashers are common upgrades in Larkspur's renovated kitchens over the past 5-10 years, with E-code faults and inlet valve scale being their most common service calls in this community."
    w_body="Larkspur is a 2000s family neighbourhood in southeast Edmonton, one of the seven sub-communities of The Meadows master-planned area east of 17 Street SE. Developed between 2003 and 2012, Larkspur features single-family homes and townhouses along Larkspur Road SE and Larkspur Boulevard SE. Whirlpool, Samsung, and LG washers are the dominant brands. At 12-22 years of service, drain pump failures, drum bearing noise, and door boot seal leaks are the most frequent calls. We carry OEM pump assemblies and bearings for all major washer platforms."
    f_body="Larkspur is a 2000s family neighbourhood in southeast Edmonton, part of The Meadows master-planned area east of 17 Street SE. Samsung and LG French-door refrigerators are the most common fridge brands alongside builder-grade Whirlpool and Frigidaire units now 12-22 years old. Ice maker module failures, inlet valve scale from EPCOR 170-200 mg/L hard water, defrost heater burnouts, and evaporator fan faults are the most common repair calls from Larkspur. We carry OEM Samsung, LG, and Whirlpool fridge parts for Larkspur dispatches." }

  @{ slug="parkview"; display="Parkview"; era="1950s-1960s"; transit="approximately 12-16 minutes from our Edmonton hub via 149 Street SW and Fox Drive"; streets="Parkview Drive, Fox Drive, and 149 Street SW"; dw_brands="Bosch, KitchenAid, Miele, Samsung"; w_brands="LG, Samsung, Bosch, Whirlpool"; f_brands="Sub-Zero, Bosch, KitchenAid, Samsung"
    dw_body="Parkview is a 1950s-1960s mature riverside community in west Edmonton where renovated kitchens feature Bosch, KitchenAid, and Miele dishwashers. River valley proximity means humidity accelerates door gasket wear and interior corrosion in dishwashers that are not regularly maintained. Edmonton EPCOR hard water at 170-200 mg/L compounds spray arm scale. Bosch E-code faults and KitchenAid control board failures are the top calls from Parkview. Heritage utility room access configurations can complicate service  -  our technicians carry slim-profile tools for Parkview renovation kitchens."
    w_body="Parkview is a 1950s-1960s mature riverside neighbourhood in west Edmonton, situated on a high plateau above the North Saskatchewan River valley. Streets like Parkview Drive and the Fox Drive corridor are lined with well-maintained bungalows and two-storey homes that have been extensively renovated over the decades. LG and Samsung front-load washers are common in these renovated laundry rooms. Bosch and Whirlpool front-loaders also appear in Parkview's higher-end renovations. River valley humidity can contribute to door boot seal degradation in front-load washers. We carry OEM parts for all major front-load washer platforms."
    f_body="Parkview is a 1950s-1960s mature riverside neighbourhood in west Edmonton where renovated kitchens feature Sub-Zero built-in refrigerators, Bosch French-door units, and KitchenAid side-by-sides. River valley proximity means humidity can cause elevated ambient moisture in utility areas, accelerating door gasket wear and condenser coil corrosion. Sub-Zero compressor issues and Bosch control board faults are the most common premium fridge repair calls from Parkview. We carry OEM Sub-Zero and Bosch fridge parts for west Edmonton dispatches." }

  @{ slug="laurier-heights"; display="Laurier Heights"; era="1950s-1960s"; transit="approximately 12-16 minutes from our Edmonton hub via Groat Road NW and 131 Street SW"; streets="Laurier Drive, 131 Street SW, and Groat Road NW"; dw_brands="Miele, Bosch, Sub-Zero, Thermador"; w_brands="Miele, LG, Bosch, Samsung"; f_brands="Sub-Zero, Miele, Bosch, KitchenAid"
    dw_body="Laurier Heights is a 1950s-1960s upscale west Edmonton neighbourhood where kitchens feature premium Miele, Bosch, and Sub-Zero appliances. Infill builds add Thermador integrated dishwashers to the service profile. Edmonton EPCOR hard water at 170-200 mg/L causes mineral scale in Miele inlet valves and Bosch spray arm nozzles. Drain pump wear and E-code faults are the most common calls. Heritage kitchens in original Laurier Heights homes can present access challenges in tight utility configurations  -  our technicians carry slim-profile diagnostic tools and are experienced with premium integrated dishwasher installations."
    w_body="Laurier Heights is a 1950s-1960s upscale mature neighbourhood in west Edmonton, bordered by the North Saskatchewan River valley on the south and the Wolf Willow Ravine on the west. Streets like Laurier Drive and 131 Street SW wind through a well-established community of renovated bungalows, two-storey family homes, and infill builds. Miele and Bosch front-load washers are common in the premium laundry rooms of Laurier Heights renovations. LG and Samsung front-loaders appear in more recent builds. River valley humidity can contribute to door boot seal degradation. We carry OEM Miele and Bosch washer parts for Laurier Heights dispatches."
    f_body="Laurier Heights is a 1950s-1960s upscale west Edmonton neighbourhood where kitchens feature Sub-Zero built-in refrigerators, Miele integrated fridges, and Bosch French-door units. These are among the highest-value appliances we service in Edmonton. Infill builds have added Thermador and Fisher and Paykel integrated refrigerators to the Laurier Heights service profile. Sub-Zero compressor issues, Miele refrigerant system faults, and Bosch ice maker failures are the most common premium repair calls. We carry OEM Sub-Zero and Miele fridge parts as standard truck stock for west Edmonton dispatches." }
